rsNotificationsMib.name: rsNotificationsMib

revisions.description: Added rsEnvirTempTooLow notification definition. This will be emitted when the temperature of a component falls below the acceptable range.
Added rsSyslog2SNMPMap notification for generating a generic SNMP notification based on a syslog message that is generated for a specified event.
Modified the semantics of rsEnvirTempExceeded and rsEnvirTempNormal in the DESCRIPTION section to match with the implementation.
Fixed a typo in the conformance section

Add two notifications for chassis that have switching fabrics. The first notification is switching fabric failure. The second notification is switching fabric failover. Add a new notification group. Add a new module compliance.
Inserted a sub-id 0 to conform to RFC 2576 Section 2.1.2(5) and renamed rstone-traps-mib as rstone-notifications-mib.

rsNotificationsMib.description: This module describes the set of notifications specific to the Devices from Riverstone Networks platform. This module represents the total set of enterprise notifications, some are conditionally mandatory depending on platform capabilities.

rsEnvirPowerSupplyFailed.name: rsEnvirPowerSupplyFailed
rsEnvirPowerSupplyFailed.description: A power supply on the sending device has failed. The entPhysicalDescr object identifies the failed supply.

rsEnvirPowerSupplyRecovered.name: rsEnvirPowerSupplyRecovered
rsEnvirPowerSupplyRecovered.description: A power supply on the sending device has recovered after failure. The entPhysicalDescr object identifies the recovered supply.

rsEnvirFanFailed.name: rsEnvirFanFailed
rsEnvirFanFailed.description: A Fan tray on the sending device has failed. The entPhysicalDescr object identifies the failed fan tray.

rsEnvirFanRecovered.name: rsEnvirFanRecovered
rsEnvirFanRecovered.description: A Fan tray on the sending device has recovered after failure. The entPhysicalDescr object identifies the recovered Fan tray.

rsEnvirTempExceeded.name: rsEnvirTempExceeded
rsEnvirTempExceeded.description: A temperature inside the chassis on the sending device has exceeded normal operating temperature. The entPhysicalDescr object identifies the module that has the temperature sensor.

rsEnvirTempNormal.name: rsEnvirTempNormal
rsEnvirTempNormal.description: A temperature inside the chassis on the sending device has returned to normal operating temperature. The entPhysicalDescr object identifies the module that has the temperature sensor.

rsEnvirHotSwapIn.name: rsEnvirHotSwapIn
rsEnvirHotSwapIn.description: A module has been inserted into the chassis. The object entPhysicalDescr identifies the module. The module can be a card for the main bay or a switching fabric in the switching fabric bay.

rsEnvirHotSwapOut.name: rsEnvirHotSwapOut
rsEnvirHotSwapOut.description: A module has been turned off or removed from the chassis. The object entPhysicalDescr identifies the module. The module can be a card for the main bay or a switching fabric in the switching fabric.

rsEnvirBackupControlModuleOnline.name: rsEnvirBackupControlModuleOnline
rsEnvirBackupControlModuleOnline.description: A backup control module that was in standby mode has taken over for a failed primary control module. The objec entPhysicalDescr identifies the now active control module.

rsEnvirSwitchingFabricFailure.name: rsEnvirSwitchingFabricFailure
rsEnvirSwitchingFabricFailure.description: The primary switching fabric that was in standby mode has failed. The object entPhysicalDescr identifies the failed switching fabric. If there is a backup switching fabric and if it comes up ok, rsEnvirSwitchingFabricFailover would be sent after this one.

rsEnvirSwitchingFabricFailover.name: rsEnvirSwitchingFabricFailover
rsEnvirSwitchingFabricFailover.description: A backup switching fabric that was in standby mode has taken over for a failed primary switching fabric. The object entPhysicalDescr identifies the now active switching fabric. This would be sent after sending rsEnvirSwitchingFabricFailure.

rsEnvirTempTooLow.name: rsEnvirTempTooLow
rsEnvirTempTooLow.description: A temperature inside the chassis on the sending device has fallen below normal operating temperature. The entPhysicalDescr object identifies the module that has the temperature sensor.

rsS2SModuleId.name: rsS2SModuleId
rsS2SModuleId.description: Name of the software module that is generating this syslog message.

rsS2SSeverity.name: rsS2SSeverity
rsS2SSeverity.description: Severity of the event that caused the syslog message to be generated.

rsS2SMessage.name: rsS2SMessage
rsS2SMessage.description: Text message describing the event that resulted in the syslog message being generated. Any instance identifiers will be embedded in this message text.

rsSyslog2SNMPMap.name: rsSyslog2SNMPMap
rsSyslog2SNMPMap.description: A backup control module that was in standby mode has taken over for a failed primary control module. The objec entPhysicalDescr identifies the now active control module.

rsNotificationComplianceV10.name: rsNotificationComplianceV10
rsNotificationComplianceV10.description: The compliance statement for the RIVERSTONE-NOTIFICATIONS-MIB.

rsNotificationComplianceV11.name: rsNotificationComplianceV11
rsNotificationComplianceV11.description: Add compliance that includes the two new notifications.

rsNotificationComplianceV12.name: rsNotificationComplianceV12
rsNotificationComplianceV12.description: Add compliance that includes the two new notifications.

rsNotificationConfGroupV10.name: rsNotificationConfGroupV10
rsNotificationConfGroupV10.description: A base set of notifications for chassis based devices.

rsNotificationSwitchingFabric.name: rsNotificationSwitchingFabric
rsNotificationSwitchingFabric.description: A set of switching fabric notifications.

rsNotificationSyslog2SNMPMap.name: rsNotificationSyslog2SNMPMap
rsNotificationSyslog2SNMPMap.description: A notification to map syslog message to SNMP.
